    "Name": "Archer",
    "Details": "During the chaos of the Amaris Civil War, many unorthodox refits were created in desperate attempts to simply get guns on the field. The <i>Archer</i> 2RF 'Flambé' was one such refit, designed for burning infantry out of entrenched positions, war crimes be damned. The reinforced actuators mitigated the risk of swarming infantry, with 2 Maxell Small Pulse Lasers and 2 Skylight Flamers able to decimate any squads that tried. The twin turret mounts allowed for the quad Zeus LRM-15 launchers to fire with pinpoint accuracy. In order to mount such an impressive amount of equipment, the Flambé is powered by a 280 XL Engine.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Stable</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.18</color></b>",
